==English==

===Etymology===
From Old English [[cēap]], ''[[trade]]''. Originally a loan from Latin [[caupo]], ''[[tradesman]]'', ''[[innkeeper]]'', whence also Old High German ''kouf'' (see German [[Kauf]]) and Finnish [[kauppa]], ''[[shop]]''.

